Ingredients:
0.5 lb Chocolate malt (UK or US)
0.5 lb Black patent malt
0.5 lb Special B malt
0.5 lb Cara-Hell malt
7.0 lbs Amber LME
1.0 oz German Northern Brewer hops - bittering
1.0 oz Fuggle hops - ½ flavour, ½ aroma
4.0 oz Italian roast coffee (whole bean)
WLP005 British Ale yeast

Procedure:
Shake and set aside yeast in a warm place.
Heat 2.0 gallons water to 145F
Steep specialty grains for 25-30 minutes
Remove grains
Bring to boil
Remove from heat long enough to dissolve LME, then return to boil

The boil (60m total):
60m: 1.0 oz German Northern Brewer hops
15m: 0.5 oz Fuggle hops
15m: 4.0 oz coarse-ground Italian Roast coffee bean (add these in a nylon/muslin bag - you’ll need to remove them at the end of the boil)
5m: 0.5 oz Fuggle hops

Place pot in sink of cold water until water in sink is too hot to touch.
Add 10 lbs ice to primary fermentation bucket
Pour hot wort over ice
Add water to reach 5.25 gallons total
Verify temperature is ~70F.  If too hot, wait to cool.
Add yeast, seal, allow to ferment.
Transfer to secondary after 2 weeks.
Ferment in secondary for 1 week, then keg/bottle.
If bottling, use Dark DME as primer.

